    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a1b2c3d4\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Landing Page Performance Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes landing page performance data to identify which pages drive the most traffic, best conversion rates, and lowest bounce rates. We explore how traffic sources, devices, and page characteristics influence user behaviour and conversions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Build an end-to-end landing page analytics workflow from raw session data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Measure and compare key web metrics: sessions, bounce rate, conversion rate, and time-on-page.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Segment performance by traffic source, device type, and page variant.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify actionable insights for improving page design and traffic allocation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Practice communicating web analytics findings clearly.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Marketing and product teams invest heavily in landing pages but often lack a rigorous understanding of which pages perform best and why. Without data-driven analysis, teams risk spending budget on underperforming pages while neglecting high-potential ones.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Landing pages are often the first touchpoint a user has with a product or brand. A 1-2% improvement in conversion rate can translate directly into significant revenue gains. Understanding bounce behaviour helps diagnose page design and messaging issues before they compound.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a1b2c3d5\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We generate a realistic synthetic dataset of **10,000 landing page sessions** with the following fields:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `session_id` — unique visitor session\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `page_name` — landing page variant (e.g. Homepage, Pricing, Product Demo, Free Trial, Blog Post)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `traffic_source` — where the visitor came from (Organic Search, Paid Search, Social, Email, Direct, Referral)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `device` — Desktop, Mobile, Tablet\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `sessions` — always 1 per row (session-level data)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `time_on_page_sec` — seconds spent on the page\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `bounced` — 1 if user left without interaction, 0 otherwise\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `converted` — 1 if user completed the goal action, 0 otherwise\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `date` — session date over a 90-day window\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This dataset is synthetically generated within the notebook for educational purposes. No external data download is required. The patterns are designed to be realistic but do not represent any real company's data.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a1b2c3d6\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Environment Setup\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We install and import only the packages needed for this analysis.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a1b2c3d7\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a1b2c3d8\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a1b2c3d9\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.set_option(\\\"display.max_columns\\\", 30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d0\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Configuration / Constants\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d1\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N_SESSIONS = 10_000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DATE_START = \\\"2025-10-01\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DATE_END = \\\"2025-12-29\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PAGES = [\\\"Homepage\\\", \\\"Pricing\\\", \\\"Product Demo\\\", \\\"Free Trial\\\", \\\"Blog Post\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TRAFFIC_SOURCES = [\\\"Organic Search\\\", \\\"Paid Search\\\", \\\"Social\\\", \\\"Email\\\", \\\"Direct\\\", \\\"Referral\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DEVICES = [\\\"Desktop\\\", \\\"Mobile\\\", \\\"Tablet\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Realistic conversion & bounce profiles per page\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PAGE_PROFILES = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Homepage\\\":     {\\\"conv_rate\\\": 0.03, \\\"bounce_rate\\\": 0.45, \\\"avg_time\\\": 35},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Pricing\\\":      {\\\"conv_rate\\\": 0.08, \\\"bounce_rate\\\": 0.30, \\\"avg_time\\\": 60},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Product Demo\\\": {\\\"conv_rate\\\": 0.12, \\\"bounce_rate\\\": 0.25, \\\"avg_time\\\": 90},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Free Trial\\\":   {\\\"conv_rate\\\": 0.15, \\\"bounce_rate\\\": 0.20, \\\"avg_time\\\": 75},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Blog Post\\\":    {\\\"conv_rate\\\": 0.02, \\\"bounce_rate\\\": 0.55, \\\"avg_time\\\": 120},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d2\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation / Loading\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We generate a realistic synthetic dataset. Each row represents one landing page session. Conversion and bounce probabilities vary by page type, traffic source, and device to create realistic analytical patterns.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d3\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(DATE_START, DATE_END, freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"page_weights = [0.30, 0.20, 0.15, 0.15, 0.20]  # traffic distribution\\n\",\n",
    "    \"source_weights = [0.30, 0.20, 0.15, 0.12, 0.13, 0.10]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"device_weights = [0.50, 0.40, 0.10]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N_SESSIONS):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    page = rng.choice(PAGES, p=page_weights)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    source = rng.choice(TRAFFIC_SOURCES, p=source_weights)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    device = rng.choice(DEVICES, p=device_weights)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    date = rng.choice(dates)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    prof = PAGE_PROFILES[page]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Device modifier: mobile has higher bounce, lower conversion\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bounce_mod = 0.10 if device == \\\"Mobile\\\" else (-0.05 if device == \\\"Desktop\\\" else 0.0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conv_mod = -0.03 if device == \\\"Mobile\\\" else (0.02 if device == \\\"Desktop\\\" else 0.0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Source modifier: paid search converts better\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if source == \\\"Paid Search\\\":\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        conv_mod += 0.03\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif source == \\\"Social\\\":\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        bounce_mod += 0.05\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bounce_prob = np.clip(prof[\\\"bounce_rate\\\"] + bounce_mod, 0.05, 0.85)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conv_prob = np.clip(prof[\\\"conv_rate\\\"] + conv_mod, 0.005, 0.30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bounced = int(rng.random() < bounce_prob)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    converted = 0 if bounced else int(rng.random() < conv_prob / (1 - bounce_prob + 1e-9))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    time_on_page = max(1, int(rng.normal(prof[\\\"avg_time\\\"], prof[\\\"avg_time\\\"] * 0.4)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if bounced:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        time_on_page = max(1, int(time_on_page * 0.3))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"session_id\\\": f\\\"S{i+1:06d}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"date\\\": pd.Timestamp(date),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"page_name\\\": page,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"traffic_source\\\": source,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"device\\\": device,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"time_on_page_sec\\\": time_on_page,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"bounced\\\": bounced,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"converted\\\": converted,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset shape: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d4\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation Checks\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Before any analysis, we verify the dataset has no structural issues.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d5\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Data Types ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(df.dtypes)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n=== Missing Values ===\\\\n{df.isnull().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n=== Duplicated session_ids: {df['session_id'].duplicated().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"=== Bounced values: {sorted(df['bounced'].unique())}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"=== Converted values: {sorted(df['converted'].unique())}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"=== Date range: {df['date'].min()} → {df['date'].max()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"=== Pages: {df['page_name'].unique().tolist()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Logic check: nobody who bounced should have converted\\n\",\n",
    "    \"bad_rows = df[(df[\\\"bounced\\\"] == 1) & (df[\\\"converted\\\"] == 1)]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n=== Bounced + converted (should be 0): {len(bad_rows)}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert len(bad_rows) == 0, \\\"Data integrity issue!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✅ All validation checks passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d6\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Cleaning\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The synthetic dataset is already clean by construction. In a real project you would:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Remove bot traffic (user-agent filtering)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Remove internal IPs\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Handle sessions with 0 duration\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Deduplicate sessions from the same user in short windows\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We add a few derived columns for analysis.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"b1b2c3d7\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"day_of_week\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.day_name()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"week\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.isocalendar().week.astype(int)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"engaged\\\"] = ((df[\\\"bounced\\\"] == 0) & (df[\\\"time_on_page_sec\\\"] > 30)).astype(int)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Derived columns added.\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d0\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Let's explore the overall shape of the dataset.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d1\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total sessions: {len(df):,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Overall bounce rate: {df['bounced'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Overall conversion rate: {df['converted'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Avg time on page: {df['time_on_page_sec'].mean():.1f} sec\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Median time on page: {df['time_on_page_sec'].median():.1f} sec\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTraffic by page:\\\\n{df['page_name'].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTraffic by source:\\\\n{df['traffic_source'].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTraffic by device:\\\\n{df['device'].value_counts()}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d2\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Univariate Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Distribution of key metrics across all sessions.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d3\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Time on page distribution\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].hist(df[\\\"time_on_page_sec\\\"], bins=50, color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Time on Page (seconds)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"Seconds\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].axvline(df[\\\"time_on_page_sec\\\"].median(), color=\\\"red\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\", label=f\\\"Median: {df['time_on_page_sec'].median():.0f}s\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Bounce distribution by page\\n\",\n",
    "    \"bounce_rates = df.groupby(\\\"page_name\\\")[\\\"bounced\\\"].mean().sort_values()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"bounce_rates.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Bounce Rate by Page\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_xlabel(\\\"Bounce Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Conversion distribution by page\\n\",\n",
    "    \"conv_rates = df.groupby(\\\"page_name\\\")[\\\"converted\\\"].mean().sort_values()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"conv_rates.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[2], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Conversion Rate by Page\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_xlabel(\\\"Conversion Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d4\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"**Interpretation:** The time-on-page distribution is right-skewed, typical of web session data — most users leave quickly while some highly engaged users stay long. Blog Posts have the highest bounce rate but also the longest average time (readers who stay, stay long). Product Demo and Free Trial pages have the best conversion rates, which is expected since visitors arriving there have higher intent.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d5\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Bivariate / Multivariate Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### How do traffic source and device interact with page performance?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d6\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Pivot: conversion rate by page × traffic source\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pivot_conv = df.pivot_table(values=\\\"converted\\\", index=\\\"page_name\\\", columns=\\\"traffic_source\\\", aggfunc=\\\"mean\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(pivot_conv, annot=True, fmt=\\\".2%\\\", cmap=\\\"YlGn\\\", ax=ax, linewidths=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Conversion Rate: Page × Traffic Source\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d7\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Pivot: bounce rate by page × device\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pivot_bounce = df.pivot_table(values=\\\"bounced\\\", index=\\\"page_name\\\", columns=\\\"device\\\", aggfunc=\\\"mean\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(pivot_bounce, annot=True, fmt=\\\".1%\\\", cmap=\\\"OrRd\\\", ax=ax, linewidths=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Bounce Rate: Page × Device\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c1b2c3d8\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"**Interpretation:** Paid Search traffic generally converts at a higher rate across pages — expected because these visitors are pre-qualified by their search query. Mobile devices show consistently higher bounce rates than Desktop, which suggests pages may not be fully optimized for mobile experience.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d0\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Feature-Specific Insights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Traffic source quality: sessions, bounce rate, conversion rate combined\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d1\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"source_summary = df.groupby(\\\"traffic_source\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sessions=(\\\"session_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bounce_rate=(\\\"bounced\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conversion_rate=(\\\"converted\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_time=(\\\"time_on_page_sec\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    engagement_rate=(\\\"engaged\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").sort_values(\\\"conversion_rate\\\", ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"source_summary[\\\"bounce_rate\\\"] = source_summary[\\\"bounce_rate\\\"].map(\\\"{:.1%}\\\".format)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"source_summary[\\\"conversion_rate\\\"] = source_summary[\\\"conversion_rate\\\"].map(\\\"{:.2%}\\\".format)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"source_summary[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"] = source_summary[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"].map(\\\"{:.1%}\\\".format)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"source_summary[\\\"avg_time\\\"] = source_summary[\\\"avg_time\\\"].map(\\\"{:.1f}s\\\".format)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Traffic Source Quality Summary ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"source_summary\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d2\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Time on page by page and conversion status\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"page_name\\\", y=\\\"time_on_page_sec\\\", hue=\\\"converted\\\", ax=ax, palette=\\\"Set2\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Time on Page by Landing Page and Conversion Status\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Seconds\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.xticks(rotation=15)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d3\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"**Interpretation:** Converted users tend to spend more time on the page, which aligns with the expectation that conversion requires reading, comparing, or filling out a form. This is especially visible on the Pricing and Product Demo pages.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d4\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Statistical Checks / Hypothesis Testing\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Is the conversion rate difference between Desktop and Mobile statistically significant?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d5\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"desktop_conv = df[df[\\\"device\\\"] == \\\"Desktop\\\"][\\\"converted\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mobile_conv = df[df[\\\"device\\\"] == \\\"Mobile\\\"][\\\"converted\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Two-proportion z-test (approximation using chi-square)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"contingency = pd.crosstab(df[\\\"device\\\"].isin([\\\"Desktop\\\"]).map({True: \\\"Desktop\\\", False: \\\"Mobile/Tablet\\\"}), df[\\\"converted\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"chi2, p_value, dof, expected = stats.chi2_contingency(contingency)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Desktop conversion rate: {desktop_conv.mean():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mobile conversion rate:  {mobile_conv.mean():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nChi-square test: χ² = {chi2:.3f}, p-value = {p_value:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Result: {'Statistically significant' if p_value < 0.05 else 'Not statistically significant'} at α=0.05\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d6\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Does bounce rate differ significantly across pages?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"d1b2c3d7\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"groups = [group[\\\"bounced\\\"].values for _, group in df.groupby(\\\"page_name\\\")]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stat, p_val = stats.kruskal(*groups)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Kruskal-Wallis test for bounce rate across pages:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"H-statistic = {stat:.2f}, p-value = {p_val:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Result: {'Significant difference' if p_val < 0.05 else 'No significant difference'} at α=0.05\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"e1b2c3d0\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Visual Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Daily traffic trend over the analysis period\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"e1b2c3d1\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"daily = df.groupby(\\\"date\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sessions=(\\\"session_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conversions=(\\\"converted\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bounces=(\\\"bounced\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily[\\\"conv_rate\\\"] = daily[\\\"conversions\\\"] / daily[\\\"sessions\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily[\\\"bounce_rate\\\"] = daily[\\\"bounces\\\"] / daily[\\\"sessions\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily[\\\"conv_rate_ma7\\\"] = daily[\\\"conv_rate\\\"].rolling(7, center=True).mean()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(14, 8), sharex=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].bar(daily[\\\"date\\\"], daily[\\\"sessions\\\"], color=\\\"steelblue\\\", alpha=0.6)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Sessions\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Daily Sessions\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].plot(daily[\\\"date\\\"], daily[\\\"conv_rate\\\"], alpha=0.3, color=\\\"green\\\", label=\\\"Daily CVR\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].plot(daily[\\\"date\\\"], daily[\\\"conv_rate_ma7\\\"], color=\\\"green\\\", linewidth=2, label=\\\"7-day MA\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"Conversion Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Daily Conversion Rate with 7-day Moving Average\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"e1b2c3d2\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Day-of-week analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dow_order = [\\\"Monday\\\", \\\"Tuesday\\\", \\\"Wednesday\\\", \\\"Thursday\\\", \\\"Friday\\\", \\\"Saturday\\\", \\\"Sunday\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dow_stats = df.groupby(\\\"day_of_week\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sessions=(\\\"session_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bounce_rate=(\\\"bounced\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conversion_rate=(\\\"converted\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").reindex(dow_order)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].bar(dow_stats.index, dow_stats[\\\"sessions\\\"], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Sessions by Day of Week\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].bar(dow_stats.index, dow_stats[\\\"bounce_rate\\\"], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Bounce Rate by Day of Week\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].bar(dow_stats.index, dow_stats[\\\"conversion_rate\\\"], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Conversion Rate by Day of Week\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"e1b2c3d3\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Page performance scorecard\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"e1b2c3d4\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"page_scorecard = df.groupby(\\\"page_name\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sessions=(\\\"session_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    bounce_rate=(\\\"bounced\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conversion_rate=(\\\"converted\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_time_sec=(\\\"time_on_page_sec\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    engagement_rate=(\\\"engaged\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_conversions=(\\\"converted\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").sort_values(\\\"conversion_rate\\\", ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"page_scorecard[\\\"traffic_share\\\"] = page_scorecard[\\\"sessions\\\"] / page_scorecard[\\\"sessions\\\"].sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Landing Page Scorecard ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"page_scorecard.style.format({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"bounce_rate\\\": \\\"{:.1%}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"conversion_rate\\\": \\\"{:.2%}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"avg_time_sec\\\": \\\"{:.1f}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"engagement_rate\\\": \\\"{:.1%}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"traffic_share\\\": \\\"{:.1%}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"})\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"e1b2c3d5\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Scatter: sessions vs conversion rate (bubble = total conversions)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ps = df.groupby(\\\"page_name\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sessions=(\\\"session_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conversion_rate=(\\\"converted\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_conversions=(\\\"converted\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"scatter = ax.scatter(ps[\\\"sessions\\\"], ps[\\\"conversion_rate\\\"], s=ps[\\\"total_conversions\\\"] * 10,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                     alpha=0.7, color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolors=\\\"black\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for _, row in ps.iterrows():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.annotate(row[\\\"page_name\\\"], (row[\\\"sessions\\\"], row[\\\"conversion_rate\\\"]),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                textcoords=\\\"offset points\\\", xytext=(8, 5), fontsize=10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Sessions\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Conversion Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Landing Page: Sessions vs Conversion Rate (bubble = total conversions)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"f1b2c3d0\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Free Trial and Product Demo pages are the highest-converting pages.** They have the lowest bounce rates and highest engagement, indicating that high-intent visitors land on them.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Homepage captures the most traffic but converts poorly.** This is common — homepages serve as navigation hubs, not conversion points. The business should ensure strong CTAs directing traffic to high-converting pages.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Blog Post pages have high bounce rates but good time-on-page for non-bouncers.** This suggests content quality is decent for engaged readers, but many visitors arrive without conversion intent.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Paid Search is the highest-quality traffic source by conversion rate.** This confirms that intent-based ad targeting works, but should be balanced against cost-per-click.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Mobile visitors bounce significantly more than Desktop visitors.** This is a clear signal to audit mobile page speed, layout, and form usability.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Social traffic has the highest bounce rate** — visitors coming from social platforms tend to have low intent, which is typical for awareness-stage channels.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"f1b2c3d1\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Synthetic data:** While patterns are realistic, they are engineered. Real landing page data would have more noise, seasonal effects, and confounders.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **No revenue data:** We cannot assess which conversions are most valuable.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **No A/B test structure:** We compare pages observationally, not experimentally. Differences may reflect traffic composition, not page quality.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **No user-level tracking:** We treat sessions independently and cannot track multi-session journeys.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **No page load speed data:** Bounce rate differences could partially be driven by page speed, which is not measured here.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"f1b2c3d2\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Prioritize mobile optimization** — Audit the Free Trial and Pricing pages on mobile devices to reduce the bounce-rate gap.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Improve Homepage CTAs** — Route more homepage traffic to high-converting pages (Pricing, Free Trial).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Re-evaluate Social channel spend** — High bounce rate and low conversion suggest social traffic may be better suited for awareness goals, not conversion campaigns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Test Blog Post CTAs** — The engaged readers on Blog Post pages represent an opportunity. Add targeted CTAs to guide them toward conversion pages.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Run formal A/B tests** — Use controlled experiments to isolate the causal effect of page changes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Add revenue tracking** — Connect conversion events to downstream revenue for true ROI analysis.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"f1b2c3d3\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Optimizing only for conversion rate without considering volume.** A page can have 50% CVR with 20 sessions — that's not actionable. Always look at absolute conversions alongside rates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Ignoring traffic source quality.** Two pages with different conversion rates might just be receiving different-quality traffic. Segment before concluding.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Treating bounce rate as inherently bad.** Blog posts naturally have high bounce rates because readers consume content and leave. Bounce rate interpretation depends on page purpose.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Confusing correlation with causation.** Mobile users bounce more — but that could be due to page design, user intent, or network speed. Observational data cannot distinguish these.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Not accounting for seasonality or day-of-week effects.** Weekly patterns can distort short comparison windows.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"f1b2c3d4\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Filter to only Paid Search traffic.** Which landing page performs best for paid visitors specifically?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Create a \\\"quality score\\\"** that combines bounce rate, conversion rate, and engagement rate into a single composite metric. Rank pages by this score.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Segment by time of day** (if you add an hour column): does conversion rate vary between morning, afternoon, and evening sessions?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Build a simple logistic regression** to predict `converted` from page, source, device, and time on page. Which features matter most?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Add a cost column** to each traffic source and compute cost-per-conversion. Which channel is most efficient?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"f1b2c3d5\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **High-intent pages (Free Trial, Product Demo) vastly outperform general pages (Homepage, Blog Post) in conversion rate.** Traffic allocation matters as much as page design.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Traffic source quality varies significantly.** Paid Search visitors convert at the highest rate; Social traffic mostly drives awareness, not conversions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Mobile bounce rates are consistently higher across all pages,** suggesting a UX gap that needs attention.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Landing page analysis is most useful when combined with cost data, A/B testing, and multi-session journey tracking.** This EDA provides a strong starting foundation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Always segment before concluding.** Aggregate metrics hide important differences between traffic sources, devices, and page types.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
